5:
Okay, so... Looks like we've gotta get
potatoes, carrots, onions...
9: Wow. Do you always buy this much?
14:
Not always, but we do have a lot of
mouths to feed.
18:
I can at least help out with carrying
the groceries. Just let me know if
you need me, okay?
25:
...Wait, are you showing your sweet
side again?
29: M-my what? I'm just trying to help—
51:
Ryunon. What will you do if you find
this person?
66:
Looks like you're getting good use
out of the gun I left for you.
69: Why? What do you have planned?
72:
I thought you'd make a good pawn.
So? How do you like your new gun?
77:
That weapon turns thoughts into
curses.
79:
It feels great to fire your hatred out
of a gun, doesn't it?
86:
You're wrong! I-I'm trying to free
Rufo—
89:
...Don't tell me you think your dog's
heart is trapped in there.
91:
Poor thing. Acknowledge the
darkness in your heart. Give in to it.
92:
...Since that animal has no power of
its own.
100:
How could you say that?! You're the
one who took everything from him!
139:
Rufo, no one knows better than me
how kind your voice is!
146:
...You're controlling the curse?
No, this is...
149:
You want me to give in? Well, too
bad...
153:
I won't make the same mistake
again. I won't look away anymore!
157:
I won't let you take Rufo or anyone
else from me again!
164:
...To think that my own creation
would be used like this—
167:
Shut up. We're taking you straight to
the Guild Knights!
170:
Oh, I don't think so... The road before
us both must continue on... But we'll
meet again, child.
185:
After all, Rufo... was with me the
whole time...
188: I'm so sorry, Rufo... I never knew...
192: You want to get stronger, don't you?
199:
And I will. I can't let anyone get hurt
again...
219:
O-of course I am.
...Just had something in my eye.
222:
Hey, uh...
There was something I wanted to
talk to you about...
225:
I'm going to keep searching for the
killer. But I'll put that bastard behind
bars—I'm not out for blood anymore.
227:
I don't want anything taken from me
again... And I don't want anyone else
to go through that, either.
237:
So... I've got a reason to stick around
here.
240: So, um... I hope that's, uh, okay...
244:
All right, well, in return, help us set
the table for breakfast.
250:
We're having breakfast curry. 
I can't wait.
